Ok, open the rear hatch.

484
00:27:52,301 --> 00:27:54,284
噢, 我的...
Oh my

485
00:27:57,276 --> 00:28:00,338
Rodney?
Rodney, 你到了么?
Rodney?
Rodney, did you make it?

486
00:28:01,938 --> 00:28:04,443
我还没有离开飞船的尾部
I haven't quite left the rear
of the Jumper yet.

487
00:28:04,583 --> 00:28:05,939
需要我提醒你时间么?
Do I need to remind you
of the time?

488
00:28:06,079 --> 00:28:09,453
是的, 提醒我吧
我们的时间很紧吧?
Yes, please do.
Remind me, are we on a tight schedule?

489
00:28:09,558 --> 00:28:11,819
显而易见
Just pointing out the obvious.

490
00:28:11,959 --> 00:28:15,263
Ok, 谢谢
我的一小步, 啊?
Ok, thankyou.
One small step, huh?

491
00:28:33,390 --> 00:28:35,338
人类的一大步!
One giant leap!

492
00:28:36,661 --> 00:28:37,774
抱歉?
I'm sorry?

493
00:28:37,913 --> 00:28:38,783
我到了
I made it.

494
00:28:38,922 --> 00:28:40,836
很好
Good.

495
00:28:41,984 --> 00:28:45,185
先看看这第一个面板
Let's take a look at this first panel.

496
00:28:48,142 --> 00:28:52,004
这是我们大约一个月前启动的
生物探测器
This is a biometric sensor we've had
online for the past month or so.

497
00:28:52,108 --> 00:28:54,300
它检查不规则的生物频率
It detects irregularities
in biometric rhythm,

498
00:28:54,439 --> 00:28:55,240
然后进行报告
and reports them.

499
00:28:55,344 --> 00:28:56,736
那它为什么没有报告那个幽灵?
Wouldn't it have picked
up on the Wraith?

500
00:28:56,875 --> 00:29:01,258
它需要大量的能量
因此我们缩小了它的探测范围
It requires significant amount of power,
so we've narrowed it's field of focus,

501
00:29:01,398 --> 00:29:03,103
只让它探测星际之门控制室了
to scan solely in the gateroom,

502
00:29:03,207 --> 00:29:05,851
本来是想幽灵或者其他外星人
figuring that was the only
place that the Wraith

503
00:29:05,956 --> 00:29:09,887
只能从那里进入城市
or any other alien for that matter,
would likely enter the city from.

504
00:29:09,956 --> 00:29:11,870
Ok, 现在这种看法是错的了
Ok, so that was wrong.

505
00:29:12,010 --> 00:29:16,393
是的. 现在如果我把范围扩展到...
Yeah. Now if I could only
expand the field to...

506
00:29:16,532 --> 00:29:18,167
我的天!
My God!

507
00:29:18,272 --> 00:29:19,385
什么?
What?

508
00:29:19,524 --> 00:29:21,472
那就是它
看!
That's him.
Look!

509
00:29:23,386 --> 00:29:28,396
它的工作原理非常类似于生命信号探测器
不过它可以区分不同的生命形式
It works very much like the life signs detector,
but it's able to distinguish different lifeforms.

510
00:29:28,535 --> 00:29:29,579
是它
It's him

511
00:29:29,718 --> 00:29:30,587
是它
It's him

512
00:29:30,692 --> 00:29:31,318
你可以实时跟踪它
You can track him in real time.

513
00:29:31,458 --> 00:29:32,466
是的
Yes

514
00:29:32,571 --> 00:29:36,990
Ford, Teyla, 我们需要两队人
我们去抓住它
Ford, Teyla, we need two teams.
Let's go get him.

515
00:29:37,060 --> 00:29:39,077
是的, 长官!
Yes sir!

516
00:29:42,243 --> 00:29:46,975
很糟糕, 非常糟糕
我不知道我能不能修好它
This is bad, very bad.
I'm not sure I can fix this.

517
00:29:47,114 --> 00:29:48,436
你可以修好任何东西
You can fix anything.

518
00:29:48,541 --> 00:29:49,619
谁告诉你的?
Who told you that?

519
00:29:49,758 --> 00:29:51,567
你已经做过几次了
You did on several occasions.

520
00:29:51,672 --> 00:29:52,506
好吧, 你是对的
Well you're right.

521
00:29:52,611 --> 00:29:55,012
那可能是件好事
我抽到了最短的麦秆
It's probably a good thing
I drew the short straw.

522
00:29:55,151 --> 00:29:57,099
差不多是这样
That's more like it.

523
00:30:08,789 --> 00:30:11,468
主电力管道已经被严重损坏了
The main power conduit's been severed.

524
00:30:11,572 --> 00:30:14,112
我也许有办法可以变更路线
There may be some way
for me to reroute it,

525
00:30:14,252 --> 00:30:17,035
让它通过副管道
so that it's going through
secondary conduits.

526
00:30:17,174 --> 00:30:19,088
就像是一种旁路那样
Sort of like a quadruple bypass.

527
00:30:19,227 --> 00:30:23,019
我在这里应该可以帮助你
标出一个潜在的副管道
I should be able to help you identify
a potential secondary conduits from here.

528
00:30:23,123 --> 00:30:27,681
我们的时间只够尝试一次
We're only going to have enough time
to try this once.

529
00:30:27,821 --> 00:30:29,769
让我们开始吧
Let's get started.

530
00:30:30,464 --> 00:30:31,648
它还在那里么, 博士?
Is he still in place, Doc?

531
00:30:31,786 --> 00:30:37,840
是的, 它还在那个房间里
自从我们找到之后就没有动过
Yes, he's still in the same room.
Hasn't moved since we located him.

532
00:30:37,944 --> 00:30:41,390
希望它还在睡觉
Ford, Teyla, 你们就位了么?
Let's hope he's still sleeping.
Ford, Teyla, you in position?

533
00:30:41,528 --> 00:30:43,477
快了
Almost.

534
00:30:46,016 --> 00:30:47,652
我的队伍已经准备好了
My team's ready.

535
00:30:47,791 --> 00:30:52,592
我们准备同时从不同的方向
冲进那个房间
We're going to breach the room
at the same time from different directions.

536
00:30:52,731 --> 00:30:55,862
如果它试图从另外一个门出去
抓住它
If he tries to get out the other door, take him.

537
00:30:55,967 --> 00:30:56,628
明白
Understood sir.

538
00:30:56,767 --> 00:30:59,028
我们两分钟后就到
We shouldn't be more than
a couple of minutes.

539
00:30:59,168 --> 00:31:01,081
很好, 准备行动
Alright, stand by.

540
00:31:27,488 --> 00:31:32,706
Ok, 我在这能做的就是这些了
能量过去了么?
Ok, that's all I can do from here.
Is power getting through?

541
00:31:32,812 --> 00:31:34,551
是的, 能量已经过去了
Yes, the power is getting through.

542
00:31:34,655 --> 00:31:37,195
噢, 感谢上帝!
好了, 我准备结束这次太空行走
Oh thank God!
Ok, I'm gonna end this EVA.

543
00:31:37,334 --> 00:31:41,579
我回到飞船, 我们把你带上
然后我们离开这里
I'm coming in,we're gonna pick you up
and get the hell out of here.

544
00:31:41,718 --> 00:31:42,935
听起来像是一个计划
Sounds like a plan, sir.

545
00:31:43,075 --> 00:31:45,023
好吧
Alright.

546
00:32:01,967 --> 00:32:06,246
没有什么可以阻止我们
前往我们的新取食场
Nothing will keep us
from our new feeding ground.

547
00:32:14,735 --> 00:32:16,405
我们都听到了, 长官
You were on vox, sir.

548
00:32:16,544 --> 00:32:20,128
我们听到了一切
然后快步赶了过来
We heard the whole thing
and double timed it.

549
00:32:20,268 --> 00:32:23,677
我们抓住它了, 少校
你会没事的
We got him Major.
You're gonna be ok.

550
00:32:34,810 --> 00:32:38,811
Peter, 我们没法停靠到卫星上
Peter, we're having trouble docking
with the satellite.

551
00:32:38,951 --> 00:32:41,247
看看你那边能够做些什么
See what you can do
from your side.

552
00:32:41,386 --> 00:32:42,847
哦, 想起来了
Oh dear.

553
00:32:42,952 --> 00:32:43,995
想起来什么?
Oh dear, what?

554
00:32:44,134 --> 00:32:47,718
当我们改变能量从缓冲区到武器的线路时
When we rerouted the power from
the buffer to the weapon,

555
00:32:47,858 --> 00:32:53,632
看起来好像我们不经意间
把通往停靠站和气闸盖的能量也引开了
it looks like we inadvertantly routed power
away from the docking station and the air lock.

556
00:32:53,772 --> 00:32:55,511
这会是个问题
That's going to be a problem.

557
00:32:55,651 --> 00:32:57,564
Ok, 我们手动操作
就像我们第一次做的那样
Ok, we'll do it manually,
like we did the first time.

558
00:32:57,564 --> 00:33:03,514
第一次你有太空服, 而我现在没有
打开气闸盖会使舱内失压
You had a spacesuit the first time, I don't.
The airlock isn't pressurised.

559
00:33:03,618 --> 00:33:08,350
那么我们... 听着,
我会回去重新改变能量线路
Then we'll... Look,
I'll go back and reroute the power.

560
00:33:08,489 --> 00:33:11,342
没时间了
幽灵的飞船已经很近了
There isn't time for that.
The Wraith ships are too close.

561
00:33:11,481 --> 00:33:12,664
我知道我在做什么
I know what I'm doing now.

562
00:33:12,802 --> 00:33:14,751
Rodney.
别管我
Rodney.
Leave me.

563
00:33:16,665 --> 00:33:18,057
我们不会这样做的
We're not doing that.

564
00:33:18,161 --> 00:33:20,561
飞到安全距离之外
然后在卫星教训完幽灵的飞船之后
Get to a safe distance,
and then come get me once

565
00:33:20,701 --> 00:33:23,171
再回来接我
the satellite has taken care
of the Wraith ships.

566
00:33:23,310 --> 00:33:23,658
Peter.
Peter.

567
00:33:23,762 --> 00:33:26,615
这是唯一的选择
你知道的
It's the only option
and you know it.

568
00:33:26,755 --> 00:33:29,816
另外, 这样我也可以先关掉卫星
Besides, this way
I can power down the satellite,

569
00:33:29,955 --> 00:33:32,008
直到它们都进入了射程再打开
until they're well within range.

570
00:33:32,147 --> 00:33:34,513
这样幽灵就不会知道
Then there'll be no way
for the Wraith

571
00:33:34,652 --> 00:33:37,540
我们已经让它重新运转起来了
to realise that we've brought
it back online.

572
00:33:37,679 --> 00:33:42,654
好吧, 我们会隐形
然后在结束后回来接你
Alright, we'll cloak and come back
for you after it's done.

573
00:33:42,794 --> 00:33:44,776
在这结束之后
After it's done then.

574
00:34:09,549 --> 00:34:13,063
很高兴看到你又能站起来了, 长官
感觉怎么样?
Good to see you on your feet sir.
How are you feeling?

575
00:34:13,201 --> 00:34:16,959
有些发麻和刺痛
被那些东西击昏之后都有这个感觉
You know, pins and needles.
Getting stung by those damn things.

576
00:34:17,064 --> 00:34:18,594
它说了什么没有?
Has he said anything yet?

577
00:34:18,699 --> 00:34:20,682
没有, 长官, 还没有
No sir, not yet.

578
00:34:26,596 --> 00:34:28,509
你有名字么?
You got a name?

579
00:34:32,163 --> 00:34:34,425
Ok, 我们就叫你Bob吧, Bob
Ok, we'll go with Bob, Bob,

580
00:34:34,563 --> 00:34:38,391
我想知道, 过去两个星期
I'm gonna need to know what
you've been doing

581
00:34:38,530 --> 00:34:43,923
你都在这里做了些什么
现在就想知道
here for the past two weeks and
I'm going to need to know now.

582
00:35:03,545 --> 00:35:08,729
如果你还没有启动
现在应该是时候了
If you're not already powered up,
now would be a good time.

583
00:35:10,712 --> 00:35:12,695
正在启动!
Powering up!

584
00:35:19,202 --> 00:35:23,515
我们在60秒后就可以预热好武器
We should be weapons
hot in 60 seconds.

585
00:35:25,533 --> 00:35:29,047
Weir博士, 我是McKay
卫星已经准备好战斗了
Dr Weir, it's McKay.
The satellite is armed and ready.

586
00:35:29,152 --> 00:35:31,587
它大约可以在一分钟内射击
It should fire within
the next minute or so.

587
00:35:31,727 --> 00:35:33,222
等着看好戏吧
Keep your fingers crossed.

588
00:35:33,327 --> 00:35:35,866
我们在等!
祝好运!
Fingers crossed!
Good luck!

589
00:35:48,218 --> 00:35:50,549
我想他现在没有心情说话, 长官
I don't think he's in
a very talkative mood, sir.

590
00:35:50,688 --> 00:35:52,602
我想知道它做了些什么
I need to know what he's been
doing and whether

591
00:35:52,740 --> 00:35:54,898
以及它是否正在向母船传送信息
or not he's been transferring
data to the hive ships.

592
00:35:55,037 --> 00:35:57,264
